org.apache.tamaya.spi

Class ListValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.tamaya.spi.PropertyValue
      • org.apache.tamaya.spi.ListValue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<PropertyValue>

    public final class ListValue
extends PropertyValue
    Class modelling the result of a request for a property createValue. A property createValue is basically identified by its key. There might be reasons, where one want to further analyze, which PropertySources provided a createValue and which not, so it is possible to createObject a PropertyValue with a null createValue. A PropertyValue represents an abstract data point in a configuration structure read. PropertyValues actually represent a tree, with additional functionality for representing data lists/arrays using indexed children names. This allows to support a full mapping of common document based configuration formats, such as JSON, YAML, XML and more.
    See Also:
